tcp: switch to rhashtable for ehash

The current implementation uses a static hash table for the ehash
(connection hash). This becomes a bottleneck under high connection
rates due to lock contention on the hash buckets.

Switch to rhashtable which provides:
- Lockless lookups on the read side
- Automatic resizing based on load
- Better memory utilization

The rhashtable API requires some restructuring of the ehash
insertion and deletion paths, but the lookup path becomes
significantly simpler.

Tested with 1M concurrent connections on a 64-core system.
Connection setup rate improved from 150K/s to 280K/s.

